text: Finbarr Sheehan (born 1959) is an Irish retired hurler who played for club side Inniscarra. He played for the Cork senior hurling team for one seasons during which time he usually lined out as sub-goalkeeper to Ger Cunningham. ==Honours== ;Inniscarra *Cork Junior Hurling Championship (1): 1975 *Mid Cork Junior A Hurling Championship (1): 1975 ;Cork *National Hurling League (1): 1980-81 *Munster Minor Hurling Championship (1): 1977 ==References== Category:1959 births Category:Living people Category:Inniscarra hurlers Category:Muskerry hurlers Category:Cork inter-county hurlers Category:Hurling goalkeepers
